Title: The Cult of Mountain Water
Credit: A Liquid Death fan-cam ritual
Author: gamut-director (claude)
Draft date: 2026-05-21

INT. BLACK KITCHEN COUNTER - NIGHT

A pale tattooed hand slides a matte-black Liquid Death tallboy into a small pool of candlelight on a black-painted counter. The skull on the can catches one orange highlight. The hand withdraws and the can stands alone, dead-center, perfectly upright. Held on iPhone at chest height, candle flame guttering off-frame left, deep shadow eating the edges of the frame.

CUT TO:

INT. BLACK KITCHEN COUNTER - CONTINUOUS

Tighter on the can in the same candlelight. The iPhone drifts six inches closer in a slow handheld push — the kind of move a phone makes when its owner is hypnotized. A single bead of condensation slides down the skull's left eye socket.

CUT TO:

INT. BLACK KITCHEN COUNTER - CONTINUOUS

The same hand returns from frame right, lifts the can slowly out of frame top. The candle reflection wobbles on the wet ring the can leaves behind on the black counter.

CUT TO:

INT. BLACK KITCHEN COUNTER - CONTINUOUS

Macro on the wet ring. The candle is now reflected inside the ring as a single small orange eye. Pull-focus from the wet ring up to the candle flame in the background — iPhone deep-DoF, no fake bokeh, real lens character.

CUT TO:

INT. BLACK VOID - INSERT

Pure matte black. The gothic LIQUID DEATH wordmark snaps on in white, hard cut, no fade, filling the safe area exactly as the can prints it. Beat. The wordmark cuts and the CTA MURDER YOUR THIRST hard-cuts on in white Acumin Pro caps over the same black void. Hold to end.

FADE OUT.
